passages.text: Mixed Results in 2Q; Product Pipeline Picking Up

2Q EPS was a slight miss vs cons driven by higher SG&A, which more than offset higher sales vs cons. Despite fears around weaker 3QTD trends, 3Q sales guidance +1-3% is in-line w/cons (+2%). Mgmt sounded very confident in their product pipeline, marketing strategy and long-term growth opportunity. 3Q EPS guidance \(0.37-0.45\) is below cons \(0.49\) driven by weaker GM, however, one-time tariff impacts from Canada reciprocal/145% China rates are weighing on 3Q GM (which will not continue in 4Q/F26). BBWI remains a "show-me" story, but we view sentiment as overly bearish, and we expect comps to accelerate in Sept/Oct as key innovation (Disney Villains, fragrance launch) roll out. In F26, we expect continued new innovation/revenue streams to drive +LSD topline growth and one-time F25 tariff headwinds to flip to tailwinds (est 15-20bps in F26). With shares trading at 7.5x our F26E EPS, we view risk/reward as very attractive.

**Ets & TP:** We are maintaining our F25E/F26E of \(3.50/3.88\). We are lowering our 3Q EPS from \(0.47\) to \(0.43\) based on higher tariffs impacts, while raising 4Q from \(2.19\) to \(2.27\) based on lower tariffed inventory. We are maintaining our \(40\) TP, which implies an F26E EV/EBITDA multiple of 7.5x.

**Incremental info from mgmt callback:** (1) Mgmt said the launch in select college bookstores was very small and not meaningful enough to the PnL to drive a change in their outlook; Mgmt does not think the launch in college bookstores is cannibalizing the core biz 3QTD; (2) Mgmt feels very confident where they are running 3QTD relative to their +1-3% guidance; (3) BBWI has been paying a tariff of 25% on product shipped from the US to Canada since retaliatory tariffs went into place early last spring, but the impact will be felt most in 3Q. The retaliatory tariffs are no longer in place as of Sept 1, which is why 4Q GM is expected to be down less in 4Q vs 3Q; mgmt said the temp tariff headwind is the 140bps difference between 3Q (-240bp) and 4Q (-100bps) headwind; (4) 3Q GM will be negatively impacted by product flowing through at 145% China rates (also abates in 4Q); (5) Mgmt feels the 4Q tariff impact of -100bps is more the run rate as we look to F26, and further mitigation is possible to offset; (6) Mgmt planning AURs to be up in 3Q, similar to 1H +LSD; (7) Mgmt sounded very confident in their ability to selectively pull-back on promos; (8) Mgmt expects fixes to the digital site design to go into place beginning (continued below)...

Bath & Body WorksBath & Body Works sells home fragrance, soaps/hand sanitizer, and personal care products through \~1,750 stores in the U.S. and Canada, and \~300 franchised locations internationally. 72% of BBWI sales in F22 were generated through stores in North America, 32% from the digital channel, and 4% internationally.

We rate shares of Bath & Body Works as Buy. After several years of sales/margin declines, sales (ex- calendar) infected positively in 2H24 and F25 guidance calls for sales growth. BBWI is demonstrating solid execution, a strong innovation pipeline (collabs, EDL, men's, lip, laundry) and abating home fragrance headwinds, all factors we believe will drive upside to conservative \(+1 - 3\%\) F25 sales guidance (implies flat comps at mid- point). We believe near- term upside to sales and resulting margin flow through will drive multiple expansion, as investors see that path back toward \(20\%\) EBIT margin. BBWI is expected to generate \(\sim \$ 800M\) in FCF this year ( \(\sim 10\%\) of mkt cap) and we expect the majority of excess cash after divs to go toward share repos, suggesting upside to \(\sim \$ 300M\) share repo guidance (we model \(\$ 600M\) ). We view the risk/reward as favorable.
Our DCF- based target price of \(\$ 40\) is based on a \(14\%\) discount rate and a 6.0x terminal multiple. Our target price represents an F26E EV/EBITDA multiple of 7.6x.

Downside/upside risks to the shares achieving our target price: (1) BBWI's sales and margins are pressured more than expected, driven by a consumer slowdown; (2) BBWI's international strategy does not work; (3) significant investments need to be made to support growth, weighing on profitability; (4) new product lines and/or the loyalty program do not take hold as expected;
Positive or adverse developments in these risk factors could cause the share price to remain above or fall below our target price.

Guide to Citi Research Fundamental Research Investment Ratings:

Citi Research stock recommendations include an investment rating and an optional risk rating to highlight high risk stocks. Risk rating takes into account both price volatility and fundamental criteria. Stocks will either have no risk rating or a High risk rating assigned.

Investment Ratings: Citi Research investment ratings are Buy, Neutral and Sell. Our ratings are a function of analyst expectations of expected total return ("ETR") and risk. ETR is the sum of the forecast price appreciation (or depreciation) plus the dividend yield for a stock within the next 12 months. The target price is based on a 12 month time horizon. The Investment rating definitions are: Buy (1) ETR of 15% or more or 25% or more for High risk stocks; and Sell (3) for negative ETR. Any covered stock not assigned a Buy or a Sell is a Neutral (2). For stocks rated Neutral (2), if an analyst believes that there are insufficient valuation drivers and/or investment catalysts to derive a positive or negative investment view, they may elect with the approval of Citi Research management not to assign a target price and, thus, not derive an ETR. Citi Research may suspend its rating and target price and assign "Rating Suspended" status for regulatory and/or internal policy reasons. Citi Research may also suspend its rating and target price and assign "Under Review" status for other exceptional circumstances (e.g. lack of information critical to the analyst's thesis, trading suspension) affecting the company and/or trading in the company's securities. In both such situations, the rating and target price will show as "—" and "–" respectively in the rating history price chart. Prior to 11 April 2022 Citi Research assigned "Under Review" status to both situations and prior to 11 Nov 2020 only in exceptional circumstances. As soon as practically possible, the analyst will publish a note re-establishing a rating and investment thesis. Investment ratings are determined by the ranges described above at the time of initiation of coverage, a change in investment and/or risk rating, or a change in target price (subject to limited management discretion). At times, the expected total returns may fall outside of these ranges because of market price movements and/or other short-term volatility or trading patterns. Such interim deviations will be permitted but will become subject to review by Research Management. Your decision to buy or sell a security should be based upon your personal investment objectives and should be made only after evaluating the stock's expected performance and risk.
